        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2181977546" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6526488109964823105">Walter is a storyteller....If you have read his other bios, you already know this. Same situation here...but I must warn you....Leonardo was a very complicated man....a genius in his art....kept copious notes about everything he thought, felt, and dreamed about....he was a scientist,way ahead of his time,and he used science in his art, and mathematics in his paintings. Walter included all the vast details, because that&apos;s the type of person Leonardo was.....and while reading this book his paintin</span>
  <span id="freeText6526488109964823105" style="display:none">Walter is a storyteller....If you have read his other bios, you already know this. Same situation here...but I must warn you....Leonardo was a very complicated man....a genius in his art....kept copious notes about everything he thought, felt, and dreamed about....he was a scientist,way ahead of his time,and he used science in his art, and mathematics in his paintings. Walter included all the vast details, because that's the type of person Leonardo was.....and while reading this book his painting fetched a $450 million dollar price, a record in the art world..... I can't recommend this book enough...but before you delve into it,and scream how boring it is, and how it's just too detailed for you....... Skip it, because you really don't have the interest or fascination for this genius......just sayin.<br /><br />I LOVED it all.... I LOVED HEARING everything about this important man in the arts,sciences,and mathematics world. Truly an amazing individual.<br /><br />If you think you are ready to read about this vastly complicated, and eccentrically interesting man....enjoy! It's quite a ride!!</span>
  <a data-text-id="6526488109964823105" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
